reviews.text: Great food but small seats
Very good beef noodle from Taiwan so to say. Will come back for more.

Beef broth is flavourful, clear and not too thick. Sour-spicy broth lacks of heat. Bubble milk tea has no taste of tea and a bad choice of milk, taste like a mix of milk and water. Fried chicken is ok, batter too thick and oily. Waited 30 minutes on Saturday afternoon, not worth the wait.

Soup is quite nice and the beef portion is good.
Price can be a bit cheaper. 
58hkd is a bit too much for a soup.
Just go with the first item on the menu (dry beef brisket noodles).
